parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or lock, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes stiff or locks
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the check engine light illuminates
and the dashboard displays error messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or locks
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the check engine light illuminates
and the dashboard displays error messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering assist, stall, or shut off, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

and the vehicle loses power steering assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the ignition system overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to increased risk of accidents.
